[1] Thailand, H5N1
Date: Thu 15 Jul 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Reuters AlertNet, 15 Jul 2004 [edited]
<http://www.alertnet.org/thenews/newsdesk/BKK245910.htm>
[ProMED-mail would like to thank Pablo Nart <p.nart@ntlworld.com> for a
similar submission. - Mod.MPP]
Thailand confirms more bird flu outbreaks
-----------------------------------------
Thailand confirmed more outbreaks of the deadly bird flu, among chickens,
on Thu 15 Jul 2004, and, now, has recurrences of the deadly virus that
swept through much of Asia earlier this year [2004] in 9 of its 76 provinces.
"Bird flu is confirmed among chickens in Kamphaeng Phet province," said a
statement posted on the Livestock Department's web-site
<http://www.dld.go.th> [Web-site in Thai; English version not functional],
referring to an area north of Bangkok.
Almost 40 000 fowl have been culled in the latest outbreaks, officials said.
Suspected cases of bird flu in chickens and ducks have been reported in 5
districts of Bangkok, and samples have been sent for testing, they said.
The results will be known in a few days.
--
